  "title": "ELV Maintenance Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Extra Low Voltage (ELV) Maintenance Engineer</strong> <br /><br /><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee <strong>preventive maintenance</strong> on ELV systems (nurse calls, CCTV, access control, PA, BMS, fire alarms, structured cabling).</li><li>Liaise and coordinate with the specialist vendors engaged for the maintenance of the ELV systems</li><li>Conduct routine inspections and testing of ELV systems</li><li>Diagnose and repair ELV-related faults.</li><li>Monitor system performance and maintain accurate service records.</li><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>safety, environmental, and regulatory standards</strong>.</li><li>Provide technical advice and updates to clients regarding system condition.</li><li>Collaborate with client and internal teams and train junior technicians when required.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Electrical / Electronics Engineering</li><li>5 years of experience in <strong>Electrical maintenance, specialising in ELV system</strong>.</li><li>Strong knowledge of ELV systems</li></ul><p><strong>Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Excellent knowledge in Electrical / ELV systems.</li><li>Strong problem-solving and time management abilities.</li><li>Good communication and customer service skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</li></ul><p>Interested applicants are requested to send your CV to: <a href=\"mailto:skh_hr@stie.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>skh_hr@stie.com.sg </strong></a>alternatively, you may apply directly via Careers Future.</p>",
